Description: Vintage Jazzmaster from Squier Get vintage Jazzmaster tone, feel, and vibe at a great price with the Squier Vintage Modified Jazzmaster. This no-nonsense homage to the past is also appointed with modern touches like two single-coil Jazzmaster Duncan Designed pickups and a modern “C”-shaped maple neck. Throwback features that provide vintage Jazzmaster style and tone include dual-circuit switching and controls and a floating-vibrato bridge — classic touches that guitarists here at Sweetwater really appreciate. And the lightweight, basswood body of this vintage offset guitar provides hours of comfortable playing.That amazing neck!Over the years, players have fallen in love with the neck of the Jazzmaster. The Vintage Modified keeps that love affair going with a classic “C”-shaped profile, bolt-on maple neck that is instantly comfortable and playable. The 21 medium jumbo frets and laurel fingerboard add to the comfort and playability and are ideal for riffing and chording. Experience the feel and response of the neck that made so many surf rock players of the early 1960's adopt the Jazzmaster as the genre's go-to electric.Rockin tone; classic style The Dual Duncan Designed JM-101B single-coil Jazzmaster pickups give you the classic, hot-rocking tone single-coils are known for. In addition, with vintage dual-circuit switching and volume and tone controls for each mode, you can explore many tonal options for lead and rhythm playing. And with the vintage-style bridge and “floating” vibrato, you can tap into all kinds of cool, fun, sonic stylings. So whether you're playing jazz or starting a garage band, the Jazzmaster is appointed with the features that throw open the doors to years of sonic exploration and all-around good times — and isn't that what music is all about?Fender Vintage Modified Jazzmaster Features: Vintage-designed electric guitar gives you killer tone and classic vibeTwo single-coil Jazzmaster Duncan Designed pickups provide great rocking toneModern “C”-shaped maple neck with laurel fingerboard offers stellar comfort and playabilityVintage-style bridge and non-locking “floating” vibrato let you explore all kinds of cool sonic stylingsDual-circuit switching and volume and tone controls for lead and rhythm modesThe guitar is in very good condition, and plays well.
